::hero
# Noma

Readable source for beautiful agent artifacts.

::button{href="https://github.com/ferax564/noma"}
View on GitHub
::
::

::summary
Three demos prove the thesis: a `.noma` source file should be readable
enough to edit manually, structured enough for agents to modify safely,
and rich enough to render into an artifact someone actually wants to
read. Each demo below ships as `.noma` source plus rendered HTML, LLM
context, and JSON AST.
::

## Three demos

::grid{columns=3}
:::card{title="1 · Agent Planning Artifact"}
A Q3 roadmap decision: options, decision matrix, claims, evidence,
risks, timeline, agent tasks, copy-as-prompt buttons.

[Open rendered artifact →](./examples/agent-plan.html)
[Source](https://github.com/ferax564/noma/blob/main/examples/agent-plan.noma) · [LLM](./examples/agent-plan.llm.txt) · [JSON](./examples/agent-plan.json)
