## More examples

::grid{columns=3}
:::card{title="Multi-file book"}
A manifest-driven book with three chapters, scoped heading IDs, alias-aware
wikilinks, single-page HTML, LLM export, and multi-page site output.

[Single page](./examples/book.html) · [Book site](./examples/book-site/index.html) · [LLM](./examples/book.llm.txt)
:::

:::card{title="Stale memo refresh"}
A narrated trace where an agent refreshes citations, updates a claim, adds
evidence, escalates a risk, and preserves unrelated bytes.

[Open trace](./examples/agent-stale-memo/trace.html) · [Source](https://github.com/ferax564/noma/tree/main/examples/agent-stale-memo)
:::

:::card{title="Agent memory"}
A memory-profile document that validates durable facts, applies block-level
updates, and renders bounded LLM recall with stale exclusion.

[Open trace](./examples/agent-memory/trace.html) · [Full recall](./examples/agent-memory/recall.full.txt) · [Recent recall](./examples/agent-memory/recall.recent.txt)
:::

:::card{title="Dark theme"}
The research thesis rendered through the alternate dark theme without changing
the source document.

[Open dark theme](./examples/research-thesis-dark.html)
:::

:::card{title="Starter templates"}
Research memo, decision record, technical spec, and agent refresh pack templates
that parse and render cleanly before you customize them.

[Browse templates](./docs/templates.html)
:::

:::card{title="Conformance corpus"}
Machine-readable fixtures for IDs, diagnostics, roundtrip behavior, spans, and
patch application.

[Browse source](https://github.com/ferax564/noma/tree/main/examples/conformance)
:::
::

## Install the toolchain

```bash
npm install -g @ferax564/noma-cli
noma init my-spec
noma render my-spec/demo.noma --to html --out my-spec/demo.html
```

Editor support:

```text
ext install ferax564.noma-language
```

Agent integrations:

```bash
npm install @ferax564/noma-mcp-server
npm install @ferax564/noma-agent-sdk
```

